[assistant] 抽取并记录信息: {"user_identity": "", "user_preference": "", "research_direction": "Assessment of perioperative beta‐adrenergic blockade effects on cardiac complications in non‐cardiac vascular surgery", "filter_requirements": "Cochrane Peripheral Vascular Diseases Group Trials Search Co‐ordinator searched the Specialised Register (January 2014) and the Cochrane Central Register of Controlled Trials (CENTRAL; 2013, Issue 12). We searched trials databases and checked reference lists of relevant articles.", "rejection_reasons": "", "other_info": "The meta‐analysis included two studies comparing perioperative beta‐adrenergic blockade with placebo on cardiovascular outcomes in people undergoing major non‐cardiac vascular surgery. The overall quality of studies was good, but one study lacked random sequence generation or allocation concealment techniques, and the other did not report outcome assessor blinding and was possibly underpowered. There was no evidence that perioperative beta‐adrenergic blockade reduced all‐cause mortality, cardiovascular mortality, non‐fatal myocardial infarction, arrhythmia, heart failure, stroke, composite cardiovascular events, or re‐hospitalisation at 30 days. However, there was strong evidence of increased intra‐operative bradycardia and hypotension."}
